HEADWORD: Anker
<hw>An"ker</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[D. <ets>anker</ets>:
cf. LL. <ets>anceria</ets>, <ets>ancheria</ets>.]</ety> <def>A liquid
measure in various countries of Europe. The Dutch <xex>anker</xex>,
formerly also used in England, contained about 10 of the old wine
gallons, or 8⟦frac12⟧ imperial gallons.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

